  <problem><img src="/static/problems/MIT/boriskor/BKimages/4-two discs on axle.png" alt="Two discs spin on common vertical axle (side view)" encrypturl="no"/><br/><p>
A thin uniform disc of mass \(4m\) and radius \(2r\) is spinning on a thin vertical axle with the angular speed \(\omega_0\). 
Another spinning thin uniform disc, of mass \(2m\) and radius \(r\), is gently lowered down on top of the first disc as shown. 
Due to the friction between the discs, they eventually begin to spin without slipping relative to each other. Below, you will be presented with 
<b>six</b> different scenarios of that event. For each scenario, find the final angular speed of the discs \(\omega\) and the amount of heat 
\(Q\) generated by the friction between the discs before the slipping between the discs stopped. <b>Note:</b> the amount of heat can be found as the difference between the initial and the final kinetic energy of the system. 
</p><br/><b>Scenario A.</b> Initially, both discs have the same angular speeds and spin in the same direction. 
<br/>
<part loncapaid="13"><br/><multiplechoiceresponse max="10" direction="vertical" randomize="yes" loncapaid="14" type="MultipleChoice"><choicegroup type="MultipleChoice"><choice location="random" name="foil1" correct="true">\(\omega = \omega_0\)</choice><choice location="random" name="foil2" correct="false">\(\omega = \omega_0\)/3</choice><choice location="random" name="foil3" correct="false">\(\omega\)=0</choice><choice location="random" name="foil4" correct="false">\(\omega = \omega_0\)/4</choice><choice location="random" name="foil5" correct="false">\(\omega = \omega_0\)/5</choice></choicegroup></multiplechoiceresponse></part>
<part loncapaid="15"><br/><multiplechoiceresponse max="10" direction="vertical" randomize="yes" loncapaid="16" type="MultipleChoice"><choicegroup type="MultipleChoice"><choice location="random" name="foil1" correct="true">Q=0</choice><choice location="random" name="foil2" correct="false">Q=\(4mr^2\omega_0^2\)</choice><choice location="random" name="foil3" correct="false">Q=\(2mr^2\omega_0^2\)</choice><choice location="random" name="foil4" correct="false">Q=\(7mr^2\omega_0^2\)</choice><choice location="random" name="foil5" correct="false">Q=\(7mr^2\omega_0^2\)/2</choice></choicegroup></multiplechoiceresponse></part>
